{"grape": "malbec", "winery": "www.12ranchwines.com", "wine": "The 2011 Malbec was not a \n\t\tplanned wine!! When picking up our Viognier grapes the vineyard owner \n\t\tmentioned he might have a little extra Malbec available and we are \n\t\talways up for something new! This wine has all the natural \n\t\tcharacteristics of a traditional Malbec. We blended in 15% of our 2011 \n\t\tMerlot to smooth it out and aged it in a combination of Hungarian and \n\t\tFrench oak. It pairs great with smoked meats, especially smoked tuna! We \n\t\tonly produced 42 cases, it won\u2019t be around long!"}
