{"grape": "pinot noir", "winery": "valleyviewwinery", "wine": "The 2013 vintage was hot and dry for most of the year and then in late September we had remnants of Typhoon Pabuk sweep through Oregon with what was supposed to be 3 to 4 inches of rain. Luckily we only had about one inch of rain which actually helped slow down ripening and gave the vines a break from the long hot summer. The rest of the fall was warm and dry with near perfect growing conditions. The year as a whole was very good. This Pinot Noir is from our new vines, featuring flavors of cherries and raspberries. The wine pairs well with cheeses, lamb and salmon. It is medium bodied and will continue to improve with age."}
